					<head>The commentary on Aristotle's Physics</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947" rend="visible">
						<summary>A commentary on Aristotle's Physics by Averroës (Muḥammad Ibn Rushd), in the Hebrew translation of Qalonymos ben Qalonymos ben Meʼir.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947">
							<locus from="1r" to="121r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Be᾿ur emtsa῾i ῾al Sefer ha-shema῾ ha-tiv῾i shel Aristo</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">באור אמצעי על ספר השמע הטבעי של אריסטו</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718" xml:lang="en">Averroës </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718" xml:lang="he">אבן רושד, מוחמד   </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The Hebrew translation is provided by Qalonymos ben Qalonymos ben Meʼir (approximately 1286 - approximately 1328), the date of composition being <date calendar="Gregorian">1300 </date>(<date calendar="Hijri-qamari">565</date>).</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">ונשלם ספר השמע הטבעי על ידי יוסף נייטו פה אלמקסם. שנת א'ר'ם' ביום שני לחדש אדר. ת'ל'.<locus n="121r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<locus from="121v" to="123v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Be᾿ur emtsa῾i ῾al Sefer ha-shema῾ ha-tiv῾i shel Aristo</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">באור אמצעי על ספר השמע הטבעי של אריסטו</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718" xml:lang="en">Averroës</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19688718" xml:lang="he">אבן רושד, מוחמד   </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Two chapters (VIII. 2, ch. i and ii) of another long recension of Averroës' Commentary on Aristotle's Physics, which is found in other manuscripts as well (i.e. <ref target="Neubauer_1891" type="number">1381</ref>).</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
